{"title": "How would you do file uploads in a React-Relay app?", "tags": ["reactjs", "graphql", "relayjs"], "creation_date": 1444561239, "score": 3, "body": "<p>I found <a href=\"https://facebook.github.io/relay/docs/api-reference-relay-mutation.html#getfiles\" rel=\"nofollow\">an explanation in the docs</a>.  You can subclass Relay.Mutation and implement the getFiles function.</p>\n\n<p>Also, express-graphql provides <a href=\"https://github.com/graphql/express-graphql/blob/6d5344a1e7c7e9bc09ce199bfe6665a254344010/src/__tests__/http-test.js#L711-L778\" rel=\"nofollow\">an example</a> in its test cases of how to handle this on the server side.</p>\n", "last_activity_date": 1474932503, "answer_id": 33064197, "is_accepted": false, "owner": {"user_id": 2653, "reputation": 9193, "user_type": "registered", "accept_rate": 65, "display_name": "Nick Retallack", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/2653/nick-retallack", "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/6703391/picture?type=large"}, "last_edit_date": 1474932503, "question_id": 33060182}